txt.en: Nedda Pinleaf can be found the Skirmish Camps of Bree, Ost Galadh, and the Twenty-first Hall.\n\nYou should return to Nedda Pinleaf.
You have encountered a creature of ill omen unlike any of the lieutenants of the Enemy you have previously faced. What does its presence portend for the peoples of Middle-earth?
Talk to Nedda Pinleaf in Bree, Ost Galadh, or the Twenty-first Hall

It is a time of ill omen. Harbingers of the Dead have crept forth from the shadows to threaten the peoples of Middle-earth, but what evil has drawn them forth?\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>NOTE: This quest will be removed from your quest log when the event it is associated with ends.</rgb>

Harbingers of the Dead have appeared in Skirmishes throughout Middle-earth.

You should seek out and defeat Harbingers of the Dead.

<rgb=#FF0000>NOTE: This quest can be advanced by completing 'Skirmish Assault: Strongholds of the Free Peoples', 'Skirmish Assault: Treacherous Wilds', 'Skirmish Assault: Beneath the World', or 'Skirmish Assault: Shadows of Dol Guldur'.</rgb>

'Oh, ho!

'That ought to teach the Dead to stay that way, I think! And whoever sent those harbingers might need to rethink their strategy while we're around!

'You've done well, [placeholder]. Let us hope it is enough!'
